---
const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What does Glu track?",
    answer:
      "Glu helps track medication reminders, dose history, weight trends, meals, water, movement, symptoms, and day-to-day progress in one place.",
  },
  {
    question: "Which GLP-1 medications does Glu support?",
    answer:
      "Glu is built for people using GLP-1 treatments across common shots and pills, including medications such as Zepbound, Mounjaro, Ozempic, Wegovy, and Rybelsus.",
  },
  {
    question: "Can Glu help me notice patterns while on GLP-1?",
    answer:
      "Yes. Glu is designed to make it easier to compare reminders, doses, meals, symptoms, and progress over time so changes feel easier to interpret.",
  },
  {
    question: "Why do people on GLP-1 track meals, symptoms, and weight together?",
    answer:
      "Many people want one record of how treatment timing, appetite, food choices, symptoms, and weight changes line up over time. Glu keeps those details together so the overall picture is easier to follow.",
  },
  {
    question: "Does Glu replace medical advice?",
    answer:
      "No. Glu is for personal tracking and education only. It does not diagnose, treat, or replace guidance from a licensed healthcare professional.",
  },
  {
    question: "How does Glu handle privacy and account deletion?",
    answer:
      "Glu links directly to its privacy policy and account deletion instructions, and you can contact support if you need help with account-related requests.",
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="bg-surface px-6 py-28 sm:px-10 sm:py-36" aria-label="Frequently asked questions">
    <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-screen-xl">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
            <h2
                data-reveal
                class="font-display text-[clamp(2rem,4.5vw,3.4rem)] font-bold leading-[1.06] tracking-[-0.025em] text-ink"
            >
                Questions people ask about GLP&#8209;1 tracking
            </h2>
            <p
                data-reveal
                style="--reveal-delay: 0.08s"
                class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-base leading-relaxed text-ink-soft sm:text-lg"
            >
                A few quick answers about what Glu is for, how people use it,
                and where tracking ends and medical care begins.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-14 grid gap-5 lg:grid-cols-2">
            {
                faqs.map((faq, index) => (
                    <article
                        data-reveal
                        style={`--reveal-delay: ${index * 0.06}s`}
                        class="rounded-[1.75rem] border border-slate-200 bg-white p-7 shadow-[0_24px_60px_-44px_rgba(15,23,42,0.22)] sm:p-8"
                    >
                        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold leading-[1.14] tracking-[-0.015em] text-ink">
                            {faq.question}
                        </h3>
                        <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-soft sm:text-base">
                            {faq.answer}
                        </p>
                    </article>
                ))
            }
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
